Installing R and RStudio

Getting ready

This course uses the R statistical software package. You should be able to carry out all of the basic tasks for this course with R. We also recommend installing the RStudio Integrated Development Environment (IDE), an application that provides many quality of life enhancements for programming in R.

Follow the steps below to install R and RStudio for Windows or Mac.

Important - you must have R installed before RStudio will work.

Install R

Visit The R Project and select the appropriate “Download R” link for your operating system (Windows/Mac/Linux) from the top of the page.

Mac

  • After clicking “Download R for (Mac) OS X,” click on the file containing the latest version of R under “Files.”
  • Save the .pkg file, double-click it to open, and follow the installation instructions.

Windows

  • After clicking “Download R for Windows,” click “base”
  • Click “Download R 3.4.1 for Windows”
  • Save the executable file somewhere on your computer. Run the .exe file and follow the installation instructions.

Install RStudio

Visit RStudio, select RStudio Desktop (Open Source License) - FREE on the left.

  • Click the link appropriate to your system (Windows or Mac)

Mac

Save the .dmg file on your computer, double-click it to open, and then drag and drop it to your applications folder.

Windows

Save the executable file. Run the .exe file and follow the installation instructions.
